---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Kenmore Oven Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Kenmore oven repair across SoCal, Elite + Pro + standard across Whirlpool, Frigidaire, LG, Samsung, GE OEM chassis. $89.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/kenmore-oven-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "How do you figure out which OEM built my Kenmore oven?",
    a: "Model-number prefix is the entry point, every Kenmore oven model number starts with a 3-digit prefix that identifies the OEM. Check the Model # on the interior door trim plate or inside the storage drawer below the oven. Common Kenmore oven prefixes: <b>110</b> (Whirlpool), historical majority of Kenmore ovens + ranges, broadest parts availability; <b>253</b> (Frigidaire/Electrolux), ovens + ranges built on Frigidaire chassis, IQ-Touch + Luxury-Glide features carry through on Elite tier; <b>790 / 795</b> (LG), 2010s+ Elite tier ovens with LG-chassis features (EasyClean steam, ProBake convection, SmartThinQ on connected generations); <b>401</b> (Samsung), fewer Kenmore ovens on Samsung chassis but exist on specific Elite SKUs; <b>362</b> (GE Appliances), historical GE-built Kenmore from the GE-Kenmore-supplier era. At service, prefix identification drives parts-chain routing + diagnostic approach. If you don't see a 3-digit prefix at the start of the model number, call us with the full Model # on the plate, we'll decode."
  },
  {
    q: "Kenmore Elite won't heat, what's the diagnostic path?",
    a: "Diagnostic path depends on OEM. We run OEM-identification first, then the appropriate OEM-pattern diagnostic. Common patterns: <b>Whirlpool-built Kenmore (110 prefix)</b>, bake element failure is #1 ($245-$345 Whirlpool-spec element), F-code decoding follows Whirlpool F0-F9 + AquaLift steam-clean patterns, Scan-to-Cook Wi-Fi on connected generations. <b>Frigidaire-built Kenmore (253 prefix)</b>, bake element $245-$345, IQ-Touch drift service pattern, Luxury-Glide rack service at 5-8 year mark, Perfect Temp Conversion diagnostic. <b>LG-built Kenmore (795 prefix)</b>, F9 temperature-runaway triangle (board, sensor, fan), EasyClean steam-cycle service (not pyrolytic), ProBake rear-fan convection, SmartThinQ module separate from control board. Each OEM has its own F-code tables, Service Mode access sequences, and parts numbers, we carry all relevant decoders on dispatch tablet. Kenmore service without OEM identification is just guessing."
  },
  {
    q: "Sears Kenmore factory service shut down, can you get parts?",
    a: "Yes. Parts for Kenmore units come from the original OEMs (Whirlpool, Frigidaire, LG, Samsung, GE) regardless of Sears' 2018 bankruptcy, Sears was the retailer, not the manufacturer. Once we identify which OEM built your Kenmore oven via model-number prefix, we source parts through that OEM's standard residential parts distribution. <b>Typical parts lead times post-Sears</b>: Whirlpool-chassis Kenmore (110/665), 1-3 days on common components through Whirlpool USA; Frigidaire-chassis Kenmore (253/417), 2-4 days through Electrolux USA; LG-chassis Kenmore (795/790), 2-4 days through LG USA; Samsung-chassis Kenmore (401), 3-5 days through Samsung USA; GE-chassis Kenmore (362), 2-4 days through GE Appliances Louisville. Legacy Kenmore (pre-2000, pre-prefix-standardization) sometimes requires aftermarket cross-reference + 5-10 day sourcing."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Kenmore, Kenmore Elite, and Kenmore Pro?",
    a: "Tier hierarchy similar to GE's Mainstream/Profile/Café/Monogram structure. <b>Kenmore standard</b>, entry + mid tier, simpler trim + knob-or-button controls, most common in older Sears-era households, typically Whirlpool or Frigidaire chassis. <b>Kenmore Elite</b>, premium tier, feature-rich with touch controls + Wi-Fi + smart features + better stainless finishes, often built by LG or Samsung in the 2010s+ era (795 or 401 prefix). Elite SKUs include LG-chassis features (EasyClean, ProBake) or Samsung-chassis features (Flex Duo, SmartThings) depending on OEM. <b>Kenmore Pro</b>, commercial-style prosumer tier, pro-style ranges + larger built-ins, typically Electrolux Icon or Whirlpool premium-division chassis, positioned against Viking/Wolf at lower price. Tier matters for parts cost (Elite + Pro parts run higher than standard) + parts lead (specialty OEM channels sometimes 5-10 days vs 1-3 days mainstream)."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Kenmore oven runs hot, calibration or repair?",
    a: "Calibration first, repair if needed, same diagnostic approach as all ovens but the specific method depends on OEM. <b>Whirlpool-chassis Kenmore</b>: Calibration Mode accessed via hold-Bake-1-second-then-adjust-with-Number-pad; Temperature Offset adjustable in 5°F increments. Free with any other repair, $95 standalone. <b>Frigidaire-chassis Kenmore</b>: Settings menu Temperature Offset same as mainstream Frigidaire; capacitive IQ-Touch panels have deep-clean service first ($95 free with work) that sometimes resolves erratic-temperature complaints via panel response recalibration. <b>LG-chassis Kenmore</b>: Settings menu Offset same as mainstream LG; F-code sequence identifies if sensor drift (not calibration) is actual cause. About 40% of 'my Kenmore runs hot' complaints resolve at calibration regardless of OEM; remaining 60% need thermal sensor replacement ($145-$215 OEM-specific pricing)."
  },
  {
    q: "Is my 20-year-old Kenmore worth fixing?",
    a: "Honest answer: usually no on 20+ year units. Kenmore units from the pre-2005 era are in aftermarket-cross-reference parts territory for many components, OEM lines moved on, parts inventories thinned. Common failures at 20 years typically appear in clusters (bake element + thermal sensor + control board + door hinge all degrading simultaneously), which turns a single repair into a multi-component project totaling $700-$1,200 on a unit replaceable for $1,000-$1,800 retail. Replacement lean. <b>Exceptions</b>: Whirlpool-chassis Kenmore (110 prefix) ranges from the 1999-2010 era often still have excellent parts availability through Whirlpool USA, single-component repair at 20 years is still economically reasonable if other components are sound. <b>Sentimental case</b>: grandmother's Kenmore you inherited, we repair cosmetic + mechanical failures honestly without economic pressure either direction. At diagnostic, we identify OEM + age + failure + give frank repair-vs-replace guidance."
  },
  {
    q: "Can I still buy Kenmore-branded appliances now?",
    a: "Yes, Transform Holdco (current Kenmore brand owner since 2022, previously Transformco 2018-2022) sells current-production Kenmore-branded appliances through Amazon, Home Depot, Lowe's, and independent appliance retailers. Current Kenmore product follows the same OEM-built pattern as historical Kenmore, Whirlpool, LG, Frigidaire, Samsung manufacture current Kenmore units under contract. Model-number prefix decoding works the same on new + legacy Kenmore. Service economics on current Kenmore match the OEM chassis underneath. Warranty service on new Kenmore routes through Transform Holdco's service network (different from original Sears Home Services but similar concept) for in-warranty units; out-of-warranty + post-warranty service works the same as legacy Kenmore, identify OEM, route through that parts chain."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Kenmore oven repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Kenmore oven pricing follows the underlying OEM chassis pricing once prefix is identified. Common bands (cross-OEM): thermal fuse $95-$155; thermal sensor (RTD) $145-$215; bake element $245-$345; broil element $265-$385; convection fan motor $285-$425; gas oven igniter $240-$340 (gas models); door hinge pair $295-$435; door gasket $195-$285; inner door glass $285-$385; main control board $345-$580 (OEM-specific); user interface / keypad $245-$385; self-clean door lock motor $225-$325; Temperature Offset calibration $95 flat (free with other work); oven light $85-$135. OEM-specific adders: Whirlpool-chassis AquaLift descaling $145 flat; Frigidaire-chassis IQ-Touch panel $420-$620; LG-chassis SmartThinQ module $285-$425; Samsung-chassis Flex Duo divider $225-$385 (on Samsung-built Kenmore with Flex Duo feature). Kenmore Pro tier runs 15-25% above standard; Elite tier 5-15% above standard; standard Kenmore matches or runs slightly below equivalent OEM mainstream."
  },

    {
      q: "Where can I find the official Kenmore manual or warranty information?",
      a: `For official Kenmore documentation, warranty registration, and authorized service locator, visit <a href="https://www.kenmore.com/support" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Kenmore support</a>. Our technicians work independently of Kenmore's factory service network - we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
    },
  ];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Kenmore Oven Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Kenmore Oven Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Kenmore oven repair across LA, Elite, Pro, standard wall ovens + range-integrated. Model-number prefix OEM decoding service specialization (110 Whirlpool / 253 Frigidaire / 795 LG / 401 Samsung / 362 GE). Post-Sears-bankruptcy service via OEM parts channels. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Kenmore", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/kenmore/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Kenmore Oven Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Kenmore oven service? Same-day across LA:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › <a href="/brands/kenmore/">Kenmore</a> › Oven Repair</div>
    <h1>Kenmore Oven Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Kenmore oven service in LA starts with one diagnostic fact: <b>your Kenmore was built by an OEM (Whirlpool, Frigidaire, LG, Samsung, or GE), and the model-number prefix identifies which</b>. 106 impressions on Kenmore oven queries in our 3-month GSC observation reflect active LA demand, and the Sears-loyal households across Pasadena, Long Beach, San Gabriel Valley, and San Fernando Valley who need Kenmore oven service need it done right, which means OEM-specific parts-chain + diagnostic approach rather than generic "Kenmore service." Our coverage includes <b>Kenmore Elite</b> (premium tier, typically LG or Samsung chassis), <b>Kenmore Pro</b> (prosumer commercial-style, typically Electrolux Icon or Whirlpool premium chassis), and <b>standard Kenmore</b> (Whirlpool or Frigidaire chassis majority). Post-Sears-bankruptcy service via direct OEM parts sourcing. Same-day dispatch. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>106 imp, strongest retailer-brand signal</b> in LA oven GSC</li>
      <li><b>OEM decoding</b>, 110 Whirlpool / 253 Frigidaire / 795 LG / 401 Samsung / 362 GE</li>
      <li><b>Post-Sears service</b>, parts through OEM distribution, not Sears channel</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Model-number prefix, OEM decoder for Kenmore ovens</h2>
    <p>Every Kenmore oven model number starts with a 3-digit OEM prefix. Check the Model # on the interior door trim plate (swing door open + look at left or right front-edge trim) or inside the storage drawer below the oven (slide drawer open, label on drawer back or cavity wall). Prefix is always the first 3 digits before any letters or remaining numbers.</p>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Prefix</th><th>OEM</th><th>Diagnostic pattern</th></tr>
      <tr><td><b>110</b></td><td>Whirlpool</td><td>Whirlpool F0-F9 codes, AquaLift steam-clean, Scan-to-Cook (connected), Whirlpool F-code decoder + parts chain</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>253</b></td><td>Frigidaire / Electrolux</td><td>IQ-Touch capacitive panels, Luxury-Glide racks, Perfect Temp Conversion, Frigidaire chassis + parts chain</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>790 / 795</b></td><td>LG</td><td>F1/F3/F9/F10/F11 codes, EasyClean steam, ProBake convection, SmartThinQ on 2018+ Elite, LG chassis + parts chain</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>401</b></td><td>Samsung</td><td>Flex Duo divider (Elite tier), Dual Cook Steam, SmartThings Wi-Fi, Samsung chassis + parts chain</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>362</b></td><td>GE Appliances</td><td>GE F-codes (F0-F9), True European Convection (equipped tiers), GE chassis + Louisville KY parts</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p>Full OEM decoder with additional legacy prefixes on our dispatch tablet. If your Model # prefix isn't in the table, call us, we'll decode the full format.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Kenmore oven failures our LA techs see most often</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Bake element failure (#1 regardless of OEM)</h3><p>Cross-OEM common failure, bake-only fails, broil + convection OK. Element continuity test confirms. Swap $245-$345 using OEM-specific part.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Thermal sensor (RTD) drift, OEM-specific F-codes</h3><p>Whirlpool F3/F4, LG F1/F10/F11, GE F3/F4, Frigidaire specific code tables. Sensor $145-$215 across all OEMs.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Elite tier feature-specific failures</h3><p>LG-chassis Elite: SmartThinQ pairing + ProBake rear-fan. Samsung-chassis Elite: Flex Duo divider + SmartThings. Frigidaire-chassis Elite: IQ-Touch drift + Luxury-Glide racks. Each uses OEM-pattern diagnostic.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Pro tier control board (Electrolux Icon / Whirlpool premium chassis)</h3><p>$385-$620 depending on Pro chassis. Specialty OEM channels sometimes 5-10 day lead vs mainstream 1-3 day.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Door hinge + gasket (10-15 year pattern)</h3><p>Kenmore oven doors vary by OEM, Whirlpool hinges, Frigidaire hinges, LG hinges all different parts despite same Kenmore badge. Hinge pair $295-$435; gasket $195-$285.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Legacy (pre-2000) Kenmore parts aftermarket</h3><p>Pre-prefix-standardization era units sometimes require aftermarket cross-reference. 5-10 day sourcing lead. We advise replacement when multiple failures cluster on 20+ year units.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Kenmore oven tiers we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Kenmore standard (entry + mid)</h3><p>Typically Whirlpool (110) or Frigidaire (253) chassis. Simpler trim, knob or button controls. Most common in older Sears-era households. Parts economics match OEM mainstream.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Kenmore Elite (premium)</h3><p>Feature-rich touch controls + Wi-Fi + smart features + better stainless finishes. Often LG (795) or Samsung (401) chassis. Parts 5-15% above standard tier.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Kenmore Pro (prosumer commercial-style)</h3><p>Pro-style ranges + larger built-ins. Electrolux Icon or Whirlpool premium chassis. Parts 15-25% above standard. Positioned against Viking/Wolf at lower price point.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Current Transform Holdco Kenmore</h3><p>Post-2022 Kenmore-branded products. Same OEM-built pattern (Whirlpool, LG, Frigidaire, Samsung contract manufacturing). Service approach identical to legacy Kenmore, identify OEM, route through OEM parts.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Built-in + wall ovens</h3><p>Kenmore single + double wall ovens. Whirlpool + Frigidaire majority historical. LG + Samsung on newer Elite tier. Cavity-specific diagnostic on double wall oven same as mainstream-brand peer approach.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Range-integrated ovens</h3><p>Kenmore freestanding + slide-in range ovens (integrated into range unit). Full range service on Kenmore range category (same OEM-decode approach, cooktop + oven covered).</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>What Kenmore oven repair costs in LA</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermal fuse</td><td>$95 – $155</td><td>Cross-OEM common</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermal sensor (RTD)</td><td>$145 – $215</td><td>OEM-specific part</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bake element</td><td>$245 – $345</td><td>#1 Kenmore oven call</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Broil element</td><td>$265 – $385</td><td>Top cavity</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Convection fan motor</td><td>$285 – $425</td><td>Convection-equipped tiers</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas oven igniter</td><td>$240 – $340</td><td>Gas-fuel units</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Main control board (standard)</td><td>$345 – $480</td><td>OEM-specific</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Main control board (Elite / Pro)</td><td>$480 – $620</td><td>Feature-tier chassis</td></tr>
      <tr><td>User interface / keypad</td><td>$245 – $385</td><td>Touch or physical</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Self-clean door lock motor</td><td>$225 – $325</td><td>Cycle-lock fault</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Door hinge pair</td><td>$295 – $435</td><td>OEM-specific geometry</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Door gasket</td><td>$195 – $285</td><td>Heat-seal</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Inner / outer glass</td><td>$285 – $580</td><td>OEM-specific pane</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Whirlpool AquaLift descaling (110)</td><td>$145 flat</td><td>Steam-clean system</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Frigidaire IQ-Touch panel (253)</td><td>$420 – $620</td><td>Capacitive sensor layer</td></tr>
      <tr><td>LG SmartThinQ module (795)</td><td>$285 – $425</td><td>Wi-Fi module separate from board</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Samsung Flex Duo divider (401)</td><td>$225 – $385</td><td>Split-oven signature</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Temperature Offset calibration</td><td>$95 flat</td><td>Free with other work</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Kenmore Pro tier runs 15-25% above standard; Elite 5-15% above standard; standard matches or slightly below equivalent OEM mainstream retail brand. Legacy (pre-2000) Kenmore parts sometimes require aftermarket cross-reference with 5-10 day sourcing lead.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>LA service areas, Kenmore oven concentrations</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>Pasadena + San Gabriel Valley</h4><p><a href="/pasadena/">Pasadena</a> · San Marino · Arcadia · Temple City · Alhambra · Monrovia</p></div>
      <div><h4>Long Beach + South Bay</h4><p>Long Beach · Torrance · Lakewood · Bellflower · Cerritos · Gardena</p></div>
      <div><h4>San Fernando Valley</h4><p>Burbank · Glendale · Van Nuys · Northridge · Sherman Oaks · Tarzana</p></div>
      <div><h4>Mid-LA established neighborhoods</h4><p>Mid-City · Culver City · Mar Vista · Palms · Leimert Park · West Adams</p></div>
      <div><h4>Orange County Sears-loyal</h4><p><a href="/irvine/">Irvine</a> · Fullerton · Orange · Anaheim · Garden Grove</p></div>
      <div><h4>Inland Empire + broader SoCal</h4><p>Ontario · Riverside · San Bernardino · Corona · Redlands</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related Kenmore and OEM-specific oven pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/kenmore/">Kenmore brand hub (all categories) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/whirlpool-oven-repair/">Whirlpool oven repair (OEM 110 + 665) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/frigidaire-oven-repair/">Frigidaire oven repair (OEM 253 + 417) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/lg-oven-repair/">LG oven repair (OEM 795 + 790) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/samsung-oven-repair/">Samsung oven repair (OEM 401) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/ge-oven-repair/">GE oven repair (OEM 362) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/oven-repair/">Oven repair service hub →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Kenmore oven repair, frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Kenmore oven service? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair in Los Angeles, Orange County, Ventura County. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
